result.execSummary:
The defendant Jason A. Guist was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting/Failing to Stop/Fleeing, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(2t).
  • Negligent Operation of Motor Vehicle, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

9:39 am cases called-16CF19, 17TR2185, 17TR2196, 17TR2197 & 17CF174. Defendant Jason A. Guist in court with attorney Amanda M. Belville.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Statement by DA Anderson-defendant would like to resolve the SEHR case and further scheduling to be done on the 2017 matters. 16CF19-Revocation Orders and warrant received by both counsel. Attorney Belville confirms receipt, no corrections or clarifications. DA Anderson confirms Chapter 950 compliance. Sentencing argument by DA Anderson. Sentencing argument by Attorney Belville. No statement by defendant. Statement by Court prior to sentencing. Court sentences the defendant to: EACH COUNT- 6 months WCJ, with Huber and Good Time Credit. To commence forthwith. Consecutive to each other. Credit of 135 days to Count 1 and Credit of 74 days on Count 2. Costs re-imposed to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. Appeal Rights Given. Court sets STC on other matters.

Defendant Jason A. Guist in court with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement stated on the record-Motion by State to amend Count 1 to Failure to respond to signal of Officer in violation of  346.04(2t) and Count 2 to Negilgent operation of Motor Vehicle off highway in violation of 941.01.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Court accepts amendment of State. Plea: No Contest to Count 1 & Count 2. Sentencing argument by ADA Anderson. Sentencing argument by Attorney Szilagyi.   Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court sentences the defendant to: SWD and places on probation for a period of 2 years. CONDITIONS: 30 days WCJ, with Huber. No Good Time Credit-No credit for time served. To begin no later than August 1, 2016. Traffic Safety school. Terms of Agent. Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan.  DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice. Appeal Rights Given.
